WEBVTT

01:14.641 --> 01:17.235
<i>[man on television]
I can't hear you.</i>

01:17.277 --> 01:20.144
<i>It's them bells!</i>

01:20.180 --> 01:22.876
<i>I've had them in my ears
for ten hours.</i>

01:22.916 --> 01:26.443
<i>Ding, dong, ding, dong.</i>

01:27.887 --> 01:30.549
<i>[man 2] Hey, sergeant.
Where's Major Lance?</i>

01:30.590 --> 01:33.559
<i>[man 3] We moved the CP back to
that stone building. The major's there.</i>

01:33.593 --> 01:35.356
<i>[man 2] Get him,
the colonel's here.</i>

01:36.963 --> 01:38.624
<i>Hold it!</i>

01:38.665 --> 01:40.565
<i>[guns firing in distance]</i>

01:48.875 --> 01:51.241
<i>[man] Colonel! Am I glad to see you!</i>

01:51.277 --> 01:55.475
<i>[man 2] Those bodies...
Get those bodies down!</i>

01:55.515 --> 01:59.212
<i>- What are you doing? Get 'em down!
- Of course. Yes, sir.</i>

01:59.252 --> 02:02.415
<i>- We've been under fire...
- I know you have, but I don't care!</i>

02:02.455 --> 02:07.154
<i>Get 'em down! Down!
Don't want those boys left up there.</i>

02:07.193 --> 02:11.254
<i>We're gonna hold this town till
the linkup does come, whenever it is.</i>

02:11.297 --> 02:16.291
<i>Today, tomorrow,
till hell freezes over.</i>

02:16.336 --> 02:18.463
<i>For their sake,
if for no other reason.</i>

02:18.505 --> 02:21.201
<i>- [man] Private?
- [man 2] Yes, sir.</i>

02:21.241 --> 02:24.369
<i>- [man] It's a hell of a war.
- [man 2] A privilege to serve with you.</i>

02:24.410 --> 02:29.040
<i>Well, God willing, we'll do
what we came here to do.</i>

02:29.082 --> 02:32.779
<i>- Ready, sir.
- Move out!</i>

02:35.155 --> 02:40.115
Pilgrim, we fought
for this country, too.

02:43.062 --> 02:44.825
Five postcard stamps, please.

02:46.399 --> 02:49.095
- Thank you. Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

02:49.135 --> 02:51.626
Thank you so much.
Have a Merry Christmas.

02:53.306 --> 02:55.274
Airmail to Kingston, Jamaica.

03:00.346 --> 03:02.041
Stamps only?

03:03.316 --> 03:04.943
[speaks Jamaican]

03:07.954 --> 03:09.512
Twenty-cent stamp, please.

03:14.527 --> 03:17.826
Excuse me, sir?
Twenty-cent stamp, please.

03:28.441 --> 03:30.033
- Rodolfo.
- You.

03:30.076 --> 03:32.067
[gun fires]

03:32.111 --> 03:34.341
[screaming]

04:11.417 --> 04:13.385
- Hey, buddy.
- Um, press.

04:13.419 --> 04:15.011
OK.

04:21.793 --> 04:24.786
- Are you Detective Ricci?
- That's my story.

04:24.831 --> 04:26.059
I heard about you.

04:26.099 --> 04:28.966
[grunts] Yeah, well,
you oughta change friends then.

04:29.002 --> 04:31.903
<i>I'm Tim Boyle. Daily News.</i>

04:31.938 --> 04:34.873
<i>- What happened?
- Read about it in the New York Post.</i>

04:34.907 --> 04:38.809
<i>They left here two hours ago along with
The Times, Newsday and every channel</i>

04:38.845 --> 04:42.804
you can get on TV with a wire hanger.
Ain't you ever heard of the early bird?

04:42.849 --> 04:45.716
- Christ.
- Go find a wailing wall.

04:45.752 --> 04:47.686
- I got lost.
- Comin' here?

04:47.720 --> 04:49.779
Find another way
for a dollar to change pockets.

04:49.822 --> 04:53.223
- It's my first day as a reporter.
- It's probably your last.

04:53.259 --> 04:55.921
Welcome to New York.
Be like Governor Rockefeller:

04:55.962 --> 04:58.658
- Come and go at the same time.
- Give me some angle.

04:58.698 --> 05:01.758
All I can give you
is an empty feeling, kid.

05:01.801 --> 05:04.929
The perp's over at Bellevue,
eighth floor peanut gallery.

05:04.971 --> 05:07.405
The victim's deader
than yesterday's beer.

05:07.440 --> 05:10.034
Heard he wasn't special
when he was breathing.

05:10.076 --> 05:13.534
My next job's gonna be stuffin'
ballot boxes on Staten Island.

05:13.579 --> 05:18.175
Remind me to vote. I live there.
Most cops do. Go home, kid.

05:18.217 --> 05:20.082
- Don't stop for bread.
- Come on.

05:20.119 --> 05:23.555
Gotta be something I can work.
Can I give you a tip on a hot horse?

05:23.589 --> 05:26.353
I'll play Santa at the PA
on Christmas Day. Or I'll...

05:26.392 --> 05:30.385
I'll pay Hong Kong Sue over on Forty
Deuce to blow your noodle like Satchmo.

05:30.430 --> 05:32.557
How about I put a story
in your hip pocket?

05:32.598 --> 05:34.691
"Good Cop Helps Poor Kids."

05:34.734 --> 05:38.465
Honest to Jesus, you get three months
of Saturdays out of it. Come on.

05:38.504 --> 05:40.972
I can't go back to scratching out obits.

05:43.009 --> 05:45.034
See those guys?
Don't turn around.

05:45.078 --> 05:49.174
They're rolling up to Harlem
to sniff around the perp's apartment.

05:49.215 --> 05:53.151
Only case that dynamic duo has cracked
has Schaefer written on the side,

05:53.186 --> 05:56.849
but maybe you'll see something.
Don't quote those gumflappers.

05:56.889 --> 05:58.720
- You need a quote, you call me.
- OK.

05:58.758 --> 06:01.249
- Haggerty, Dillard!
- Yeah, what's up?

06:01.294 --> 06:05.321
- Take this guy uptown with you.
- Thank you. Thank you.

06:05.365 --> 06:07.890
- Come on.
- All right.

06:19.178 --> 06:22.238
We'll start in the living room
and work our way back.

06:24.417 --> 06:26.510
Close the door behind you, kid.

06:49.108 --> 06:51.440
This perp is very, very religious.

06:51.477 --> 06:54.913
Nothing wrong with being
in good standing with the Lord.

06:59.852 --> 07:02.377
And a war hero, too.
Look at this, a Purple Heart.

07:02.422 --> 07:05.482
Hey, Keith, the Brown Bomber.

07:05.525 --> 07:09.359
[Keith] Muhammad Ali would've knocked
him out. Way too fast for Joe Louis.

07:09.395 --> 07:11.295
He can run, but he can't hide.

07:22.575 --> 07:25.203
Hey, Dan, what the hell is this?

07:25.244 --> 07:28.805
- [Dan] What you got there?
- I don't know. It's heavy.

07:28.848 --> 07:32.807
Whatever this is, it ain't junior-grade.
This thing looks expensive.

07:32.852 --> 07:38.620
My wife claws around flea markets
looking for this crap every weekend.

07:38.658 --> 07:40.523
I'm telling you, this ain't normal.

07:40.560 --> 07:42.255
This definitely ain't normal.

07:42.295 --> 07:45.162
- Back up, buddy.
- Sorry.

07:45.198 --> 07:46.722
[Keith] No problem.

07:46.766 --> 07:49.564
- Professor Brooks?
- Yes.

07:51.737 --> 07:56.572
I get a lot of these things.
Old rocks. Antique specials.

07:56.609 --> 07:59.510
It seems like every
schmuck in the world

07:59.545 --> 08:03.572
who finds a backyard arrowhead
mistakes me for Iris.

08:03.616 --> 08:05.049
Put it here.

08:05.084 --> 08:09.748
From Greek mythology.
She is the faithful voice of Zeus.

08:09.789 --> 08:14.453
She flies from place to place
and commands respect

08:14.494 --> 08:17.895
from mortals and from im...

08:19.799 --> 08:21.426
...immortals.

08:23.836 --> 08:26.964
- Where the hell'd you get this?
- From a perp's apartment.

08:27.006 --> 08:29.270
- It's got this mark...
- Don't touch it.

08:29.308 --> 08:35.008
This is over 450 years old.

08:35.047 --> 08:38.847
It's the missing Primavera
from the Santa Trinita.

08:38.885 --> 08:41.352
<i>Is that the Niña, the Pinta
or the Santa Maria?</i>

08:41.386 --> 08:43.446
Oh, for God sakes, detective.

08:43.489 --> 08:46.481
It's the oldest elliptic

08:46.526 --> 08:49.893
arch bridge in the world.

08:49.929 --> 08:53.456
It's in Florence, Italy.

08:53.499 --> 08:55.763
Built by Ammanati.

08:55.801 --> 08:59.202
This was one of four statues on it.

08:59.238 --> 09:04.073
The Primavera, meaning "spring."

09:04.110 --> 09:05.941
This head has been missing

09:05.978 --> 09:10.608
since the Nazis blew up
the bridge in 1944.

09:10.650 --> 09:15.883
My God! This is a gold mine!

09:16.689 --> 09:18.680
A gold mine!

09:23.296 --> 09:24.820
Yo!

09:30.636 --> 09:32.501
[elevator dings]

09:43.716 --> 09:47.482
Merry Christmas. From Tim Boyle.

09:47.520 --> 09:49.613
Oh, wise guy.

10:18.417 --> 10:20.612
[Tim] Mr. Hector Negron?

10:32.898 --> 10:34.991
[children shouting]

10:55.054 --> 10:57.454
[in Italian]
Darling, come back to bed.

10:57.490 --> 10:58.980
Please. Enough.

10:59.025 --> 11:01.687
I need a little break, OK, baby?

11:07.199 --> 11:10.100
[Tim] They say you haven't
spoken or eaten in two days.

11:10.136 --> 11:13.162
They'll try to force-feed you.

11:13.205 --> 11:15.503
Make you rise, like Jesus.

11:21.981 --> 11:24.950
Come on. I've hiked all over
New York asking about you.

11:24.984 --> 11:27.782
I talked to everybody.
Cops, your sister.

11:27.820 --> 11:31.381
Spoke to your cousin in San Juan.
You're clean as a board of health.

11:31.424 --> 11:34.086
You got no kids, no debts, no enemies.

11:34.126 --> 11:36.253
Four years in the service. Purple Heart.

11:36.295 --> 11:38.661
Twenty-five years
of a great marriage,

11:38.698 --> 11:41.963
till your wife's heart gave out.

11:43.569 --> 11:47.562
So why you stick a German Luger
in a guy's chest

11:47.606 --> 11:51.940
three months short of your retirement?
Five million dollars.

11:51.977 --> 11:54.946
That's how much that head would
draw on the black market.

11:54.980 --> 11:58.677
What's it doin' buried there
on the bottom of your closet?

12:06.525 --> 12:08.925
You're looking at 25 to life, pal.

12:08.961 --> 12:12.453
Unless you can afford a lawyer,
you're gonna swallow happy pills

12:12.498 --> 12:15.296
in this nuthouse the rest of your life.

12:15.334 --> 12:20.101
But my story could help you.
And you need help, mac.

12:24.510 --> 12:29.106
[woman, in Italian] Enrico, what kind
of art dealer specializes in Nazi art?

12:29.148 --> 12:31.981
Because it's a lucrative business.

12:34.220 --> 12:37.189
[in Italian] You Americans love work
more than you love 'love.'

12:37.223 --> 12:38.383
[groans]

12:39.859 --> 12:42.794
[in Italian] My love,
are you ignoring me?

12:44.597 --> 12:46.394
[Keith] Pina, no.
Don't come over here.

12:49.668 --> 12:52.102
[in Italian] Enrico, you said
you only needed ten minutes.

12:52.138 --> 12:55.005
I gotta catch up. World might've
ended, I wouldn't know

12:55.040 --> 12:58.237
'cause we've been going at it
two days. For crying out loud.

12:58.277 --> 13:00.245
[in Italian] The world is still here.

13:00.279 --> 13:01.610
You and I are still here.

13:01.647 --> 13:03.342
Baby, not right now.

13:04.450 --> 13:06.975
There you go. Excuse me.

13:08.154 --> 13:09.621
OK?

13:11.924 --> 13:14.654
Oh, God. Oh, that feels good.

13:15.628 --> 13:17.493
[Pina giggling]

13:19.698 --> 13:21.165
You're killing me, baby.

13:21.200 --> 13:23.361
[in Italian] Yes, I love you to death.

13:56.302 --> 13:58.031
[sighs]

14:15.554 --> 14:17.454
I...

14:18.891 --> 14:21.883
Hmm? What is it, Mr. Negron?

14:24.697 --> 14:26.130
I... I know.

14:27.766 --> 14:28.892
You know what?

14:34.840 --> 14:37.400
I know who the sleeping man is!

14:37.443 --> 14:41.846
- [Tim] You know what?
- I know who the sleeping man is.

14:41.881 --> 14:45.476
[bells tolling]

14:45.517 --> 14:48.918
[child yelling in Italian]

15:47.913 --> 15:51.940
[man whimpering]
Mama. I want mama.

16:15.274 --> 16:18.710
Kill me now! Kill me now,
I wanna go home to my mama!

16:18.744 --> 16:22.111
I don't wanna be here.
I wanna go home!

16:22.147 --> 16:25.378
Kill me now! Kill me now!

16:25.417 --> 16:29.547
Oh, Jesus, I want my mama!
I don't wanna die! I don't wanna die!

16:29.588 --> 16:30.680
Shh!

16:30.723 --> 16:34.386
- Hector, shut him the fuck up.
- Yes, sir.

16:34.426 --> 16:37.418
- I don't wanna die!
- Shut the fuck up!

16:37.463 --> 16:42.230
[whispering] You wanna get us all
killed? That's your mama right now.

16:42.267 --> 16:45.361
- This far enough?
- Keep movin'.

16:45.404 --> 16:50.637
- You doin' fine, big fella.
- Help me, Lord. Help me, Lord.

16:50.676 --> 16:53.474
Help me, Lord,
I'm prepared for Thee.

16:53.512 --> 16:56.879
- Get off of me, sniper bait!
- Bishop, Train, switch flanks.

16:56.915 --> 16:59.247
Bishop, take outer.
Train, take the inner.

16:59.284 --> 17:01.081
- What's that?
- Take inner flank.

17:01.120 --> 17:03.680
- What's that?
- Come on. Switch places, dummy.

17:03.722 --> 17:05.212
Gimme some room.

17:09.161 --> 17:12.324
Hey, Bishop.
Why we got to cross this river?

17:12.364 --> 17:14.627
They sellin' hoecakes
and beer on the other side.

17:14.665 --> 17:15.758
[laughs]

17:18.804 --> 17:22.262
- My good luck charm gives me strength.
- Piece of shit you found

17:22.307 --> 17:24.468
in the gutter in Florence?

17:24.510 --> 17:27.502
Couldn't draw a bowl of turtle soup
from Uncle Amos with that.

17:27.546 --> 17:28.911
Worth more than a bowl of soup!

17:28.947 --> 17:30.847
Shh!

17:30.883 --> 17:32.851
Train.

17:32.885 --> 17:36.753
Hector, you speak Italian.
Cut-off head worth somethin'?

17:36.789 --> 17:39.724
<i>- Yo speaky Puerto Rican, man.
- Hey, muzzle that.</i>

17:39.758 --> 17:41.225
Keep moving.

18:51.730 --> 18:53.163
[man speaks German]

18:53.198 --> 18:56.895
<i>[man on radio] Germany calling,
Germany calling.</i>

18:56.935 --> 18:59.768
<i>Guten morgen, 92nd Division.</i>

18:59.805 --> 19:03.707
Buffalo soldiers, welcome to the war.

19:03.742 --> 19:07.508
<i>[woman on loudspeaker]
We've been waiting for you.</i>

19:07.546 --> 19:11.676
<i>Do you know our German Wehrmacht
has been here digging bunkers</i>

19:11.717 --> 19:15.619
<i>for six months on the Gothic Line?
Waiting.</i>

19:15.654 --> 19:20.591
<i>Your white commanders
won't tell you that, of course.</i>

19:20.626 --> 19:25.620
<i>Why? Because they
don't care if you die.</i>

19:25.664 --> 19:26.722
[whimpering]

19:26.765 --> 19:30.292
<i>But the German people have
nothing against the Negro.</i>

19:30.335 --> 19:34.271
That's why I'm warning you now,
with all my heart and soul.

19:34.306 --> 19:36.968
Save yourself, Negro brothers.

19:37.009 --> 19:40.308
<i>Why die for a nation
that doesn't want you?</i>

19:40.345 --> 19:44.645
<i>A nation that treats you like a slave.</i>

19:44.683 --> 19:46.150
<i>Did I say slave?</i>

19:46.185 --> 19:48.983
Yes, I did.

19:49.021 --> 19:52.286
[speaking German]
Why don't they shut her up?

19:52.324 --> 19:54.155
What is she saying?

19:54.193 --> 19:57.219
Berlin can afford to pipe
that garbage all the way here

19:57.262 --> 19:59.321
but can't give us potato soup.

20:01.867 --> 20:04.427
Individual guns only, on my command.

20:06.171 --> 20:09.629
We have enough ammo
for an hour, maybe two.

20:09.675 --> 20:11.870
<i>[woman] Look around you.</i>

20:11.910 --> 20:15.846
<i>Do you see any white soldiers
in the river next to you?</i>

20:15.881 --> 20:20.477
<i>Are they sending any white
soldiers to die with you today?</i>

20:20.519 --> 20:23.579
<i>- Of course not!
- [man] Steady, ya'll. Adolf Hitler.</i>

20:23.622 --> 20:26.614
Spreadin' that nonsense.
Don't believe a word of that!

20:26.658 --> 20:30.253
Lyin' bastard thinks we monkeys,
apes, baboons, subhuman.

20:31.363 --> 20:32.625
Show him who we are.

20:32.664 --> 20:34.598
[woman] Think of your poor children,

20:34.633 --> 20:38.433
your families suffering at home.

20:38.470 --> 20:41.371
<i>The American white man</i>

20:41.406 --> 20:44.864
<i>is raping your wives and daughters.</i>

20:44.910 --> 20:48.402
<i>Jody is busy right now in your
bedroom, with your wife,</i>

20:48.447 --> 20:53.077
<i>your daughters, even your sons.
And who will stop him if you die today?</i>

20:53.118 --> 20:56.212
<i>Do you think the profitmongers
in Washington, D.C.</i>

20:56.255 --> 21:01.784
<i>care about your children?
They're not thinking of your children!</i>

21:01.827 --> 21:03.852
<i>They're home right now.</i>

21:03.895 --> 21:09.060
Asleep, in a nice warm bed.

21:10.669 --> 21:13.137
<i>Think about the sacrifice
you're making,</i>

21:13.171 --> 21:17.267
<i>just for the privilege of being
second-class citizens back home.</i>

21:17.309 --> 21:19.971
<i>Where can you vote?</i>

21:20.012 --> 21:23.448
<i>Come to the winning side</i>

21:23.482 --> 21:27.043
<i>and, please, teach me those dances.</i>

21:27.085 --> 21:30.714
<i>That Lindy Hop and the Black Bottom.</i>

21:30.756 --> 21:33.281
<i>War is folly, boys.</i>

21:33.325 --> 21:37.261
Better to drop your guns,
give up and dance!

21:37.296 --> 21:41.926
<i>Come out of that cold water, cats!</i>

21:42.601 --> 21:44.831
[speaking German]
You got any more biscuits?

21:44.870 --> 21:45.894
No.

21:45.937 --> 21:47.495
- Or anything else?
- Not for you.

21:47.539 --> 21:49.666
I'll give you money
for a vitamin biscuit.

21:49.708 --> 21:51.369
Go over and beg the Blacks.

21:53.445 --> 21:56.346
What about you?
You a replacement?

21:57.316 --> 21:59.079
65th Army Corps.

21:59.117 --> 22:01.847
I thought they were freezing
their asses off in Russia.

22:01.887 --> 22:03.445
- So?
- You got any biscuits?

22:03.488 --> 22:04.682
No.

22:04.723 --> 22:07.021
They must have given you something.

22:07.059 --> 22:08.720
If I die, you can have all my rations,

22:08.760 --> 22:10.557
but for now,
SHUT THE FUCK UP!!!

22:10.595 --> 22:13.029
I got a hole in my stomach.

22:13.065 --> 22:17.365
<i>[woman] Come on over.
Feel the warmth of the German people.</i>

22:17.402 --> 22:21.099
[speaking German] I can't hear a thing
over that damn whore's prattling.

22:21.139 --> 22:25.200
<i>[woman] We have hot food,
fried chicken,</i>

22:25.243 --> 22:29.543
<i>greens, candied yams
and even delicious biscuits</i>

22:29.581 --> 22:32.914
<i>straight from the oven,
just like your mama cooks.</i>

22:32.951 --> 22:35.579
Hey, boys.

22:35.620 --> 22:40.751
I have two big white biscuits
right here for you.

22:40.792 --> 22:46.697
<i>Buffalo soldiers. Hey, cool cats.</i>

22:46.732 --> 22:49.701
<i>Do I have something
special for you.</i>

22:49.735 --> 22:53.136
<i>And you can have all you want.</i>

22:53.171 --> 22:57.107
That goddamned bitch
is gonna start a race riot.

22:57.142 --> 23:00.407
Is that a white woman, officer?
What's your name, soldier?

23:00.445 --> 23:03.437
- Lieutenant Birdsong, sir.
- Who is that?

23:03.482 --> 23:05.473
- You heard of Tokyo Rose, sir?
- Yeah.

23:05.517 --> 23:09.749
This is the Kraut version. Axis Sally.
She visits us from time to time.

23:09.788 --> 23:11.847
- Is she American?
- Don't know, sir.

23:11.890 --> 23:15.519
<i>[Axis Sally] Have you ever wondered
how it felt to be free?</i>

23:15.560 --> 23:21.123
<i>To be your own man?
To stand tall?</i>

23:21.166 --> 23:24.727
Need a sniper to splat that nag's
brains all over the Serchio.

23:24.770 --> 23:28.228
I can't see a thing outta these.
Roust me up a better set of cans.

23:28.273 --> 23:30.764
Right now, and a drink of water,
on the double.

23:30.809 --> 23:32.401
Yes, sir.

23:32.444 --> 23:35.777
[man] Negative, Abel Six. Stay firm
and await further commands. Over.

23:35.814 --> 23:38.339
What's he gonna do,
give her a smack on the lips?

23:38.383 --> 23:42.547
He sets himself up a mile away with fire
control, then complains he can't see.

23:42.587 --> 23:44.987
Oughta be with his men
like a real captain.

23:45.023 --> 23:47.116
He ain't been here
long enough to learn.

23:47.159 --> 23:50.617
Yeah, and you won't be here
long neither, listenin' to him.

23:50.662 --> 23:52.254
[speaks German]
Stupid white man.

23:53.999 --> 23:57.696
Right now!
Let's go, goddamn it.

24:00.439 --> 24:03.237
New cans, fresh H2O, sir.

24:03.275 --> 24:06.403
<i>[Axis Sally] Buffalo soldiers,</i>

24:06.445 --> 24:09.608
<i>take the first step, fellas.</i>

24:09.648 --> 24:12.549
<i>We have warm fires. Pretty...</i>

24:12.584 --> 24:15.314
- Hold that.
- Yes, sir.

24:15.353 --> 24:18.550
Next time I want you
to take the caps off.

24:18.590 --> 24:19.682
Yes, sir.

24:19.724 --> 24:24.058
<i>German Frauleins like big strong bucks</i>

24:24.095 --> 24:26.495
more than lollipops.

24:26.531 --> 24:29.159
<i>And we love lollipops.</i>

24:29.201 --> 24:31.260
She the one selling
hoecakes and beer?

24:31.303 --> 24:33.294
Your brain's had a rough shuffle.

24:33.338 --> 24:36.171
For the last time, muzzle that shit!

24:36.208 --> 24:37.903
- [machine gun fire]
- Coming down!

24:37.943 --> 24:40.411
- Let's go!
- Suppressing fire!

24:42.180 --> 24:43.738
[screaming]

24:48.220 --> 24:50.085
[yelling]

24:56.394 --> 24:57.986
Withdraw! Withdraw!

25:14.112 --> 25:16.376
[man] Withdraw! Withdraw!

25:19.718 --> 25:21.208
[grunts]

25:32.030 --> 25:35.796
Come on, Train! Come on, move!
Go, go, go, go, go!

25:39.638 --> 25:41.503
[man screaming]

25:51.449 --> 25:52.575
Fire!

25:54.686 --> 25:56.449
Fire!

26:02.427 --> 26:06.955
George Company. Request artillery
to grids four, seven, nine and 1-6!

26:06.998 --> 26:09.432
<i>- Send the mail!
- Where the hell are you?</i>

26:09.467 --> 26:10.957
- We've crossed!
- You what?

26:11.002 --> 26:12.697
We're with Uncle Jerry!

26:12.737 --> 26:16.195
Put smoke, H.A. to grids four,
seven, nine and 1-6!

26:16.241 --> 26:19.267
It's impossible to be
on the other side of that river.

26:19.311 --> 26:23.407
- Is that Huggs calling out a grid?
- Huggs! What is your position?

26:23.448 --> 26:27.316
Sir! Huggs is down!
Stamps here! Send the mail!

26:27.352 --> 26:31.118
- Send the mail now!
- Write this name down. Stamps.

26:31.156 --> 26:32.919
Stamps. He's across?

26:36.461 --> 26:38.361
He's lying.

26:38.396 --> 26:41.661
Now, set fire to grids two-three,
two-four and two-five.

26:41.700 --> 26:45.568
- That's Rudden, Fox Company.
- George Company? They've crossed?

26:45.604 --> 26:48.300
I'm new to this outfit
doesn't mean I gotta argue

26:48.340 --> 26:53.141
with goddamn second lieutenants acting
like uppity Negroes. You follow me?

26:54.579 --> 26:56.308
Do you follow me, soldier?

26:56.348 --> 26:59.681
Yes, sir.

26:59.718 --> 27:02.812
Smoke and fire to grids
two-three, two-four, two-five.

27:02.854 --> 27:05.118
- Sir.
- Smoke and fire to grids two-three,

27:05.156 --> 27:08.523
- two-four, two five. Over!
- Smoke and fire to grids two-three,

27:08.560 --> 27:10.790
- two-four and two-five!
- [grunts]

27:10.829 --> 27:13.297
Adolf Hitler, this is for you.

27:15.300 --> 27:17.131
What the hell!

27:19.804 --> 27:21.328
Radio!

27:21.373 --> 27:23.364
- Withdraw!
- Withdrawing!

27:23.408 --> 27:26.639
[Stamps] Cease fire! Cease...

27:26.678 --> 27:29.044
Adjust fire! Adjust fire!

27:29.080 --> 27:30.741
I repeat, adjust fire!

27:30.782 --> 27:35.583
Request artillery to grids four,
seven, nine and 1-6! Send the mail!

27:35.620 --> 27:37.110
[speaks German]

27:37.155 --> 27:38.417
Fire!

27:39.257 --> 27:40.554
[screaming]

27:42.661 --> 27:44.253
Fire!

27:51.069 --> 27:52.730
Incoming!

28:00.478 --> 28:01.638
[screams]

28:09.821 --> 28:11.618
[screaming]

28:11.656 --> 28:13.385
Get off me!

28:13.425 --> 28:14.915
Help!

28:16.695 --> 28:19.721
Help! Help!

28:39.617 --> 28:41.141
Cover me!

28:55.633 --> 28:57.191
[screaming]

29:46.618 --> 29:49.985
[both panting]

30:00.131 --> 30:02.099
[distant artillery firing]

30:43.942 --> 30:46.536
Come on. Come on.

30:59.490 --> 31:03.551
OK. You and me gotta
get to that tree. OK?

31:03.595 --> 31:05.460
- All right.
- Go!

31:08.466 --> 31:10.991
Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

31:14.372 --> 31:16.704
Get down, get down, get down!

31:20.245 --> 31:21.940
[artillery whistling]

31:22.947 --> 31:24.778
[grunting]

31:26.885 --> 31:28.978
[yelling] Oh! Oh, Lord!

31:29.020 --> 31:32.786
Oh, I'm coming up yonder!
Meet me, Jesus!

31:32.824 --> 31:35.019
- Shut up.
- Oh, Bishop, they got you, too.

31:35.059 --> 31:38.256
- No. Listen!
- Is we dead, Bishop? We dead?

31:38.296 --> 31:41.231
No, listen to me. You was dead.
OK? But I brung ya back.

31:41.266 --> 31:45.134
You ain't dyin' till I get my
money. You owe me $1,400.

31:48.907 --> 31:53.071
Look here. Go check out that
haystack. That shit is moving.

31:54.212 --> 31:55.736
What in the world?

32:02.186 --> 32:03.346
[in Italian] Arturo!

32:04.389 --> 32:06.380
Arturo, where are you?

32:08.426 --> 32:10.360
Arturo!

32:12.630 --> 32:14.029
Arturo.

32:31.983 --> 32:34.110
[in Italian] Beautiful.

32:34.152 --> 32:35.779
Where did you find it?

32:42.427 --> 32:44.088
Watch me throw it.

32:47.098 --> 32:49.089
<i>[singing] # Little black face</i>

32:49.133 --> 32:50.964
<i># Beautiful Abyssinian</i>

32:51.002 --> 32:54.597
<i># Wait and hope,
The hour is already near</i>

32:54.639 --> 32:56.368
<i># When we will be</i>

32:56.407 --> 32:58.307
<i># Close to you</i>

32:58.343 --> 33:01.506
<i># And there to give you
a different law and a different King #</i>

33:06.818 --> 33:10.185
Arturo! Now, I am nine years old.

33:22.033 --> 33:23.762
Move, sniper bait, go!

33:36.881 --> 33:41.750
[boy speaking Italian] Okay,
maybe I'm eight. I'm really only eight.

33:41.786 --> 33:43.310
[boy groaning]

34:02.540 --> 34:05.168
Good God!

34:05.209 --> 34:08.371
[in Italian] A Chocolate Giant.

34:11.581 --> 34:13.708
- [grunting]
- [in Italian] Help me.

34:13.751 --> 34:16.719
I'll give you a banana,
Chocolate Giant.

34:16.754 --> 34:18.654
[both grunting]

34:20.690 --> 34:24.559
Sorry, boy. I done gived it
every muscle I got.

34:24.594 --> 34:27.462
[in Italian] Use your tail,
Chocolate Giant.

34:32.870 --> 34:35.498
Jesus is waitin' on you, child.

34:36.808 --> 34:39.902
This world ain't worth
a pinch of snuff nohow.

34:41.545 --> 34:44.036
[in Italian] No, please don't leave.

34:44.081 --> 34:46.777
Oh, my God, it hurts.

34:52.090 --> 34:54.752
Come on. Come on.

35:01.799 --> 35:03.733
[straining]

35:07.205 --> 35:09.196
[straining, yelling]

35:14.612 --> 35:16.876
[gasping]

35:20.251 --> 35:23.015
Boy! Hey, boy! Hey!

35:23.054 --> 35:25.318
Boy. You breathin'?

35:26.791 --> 35:29.988
[in Italian] Giant,
you don't taste like chocolate.

35:53.050 --> 35:54.449
[in German]
Don't shoot. Don't shoot.

35:55.653 --> 35:57.052
You can't kill me.

35:58.022 --> 35:59.250
I'm invisible!

36:40.932 --> 36:44.299
Come on, boy. Come on.

36:44.335 --> 36:45.461
Let's go.

36:46.270 --> 36:48.295
[artillery shrieking]

36:54.478 --> 36:57.242
[Bishop] Train! Train!

36:57.281 --> 36:59.146
[whispering] Oh, no.

37:23.107 --> 37:25.974
Where's Train?

37:26.010 --> 37:28.376
He ain't...
He ain't make it.

37:28.412 --> 37:31.643
That nigger's dumber than a dime.
You sent him over the hill?

37:31.682 --> 37:34.480
- I ain't tell him to risk his life.
- It's nobody's fault.

37:34.518 --> 37:36.543
That boy was born over the hill.

37:39.323 --> 37:41.018
[Bishop] Follow me.

37:58.476 --> 38:01.274
<i>- [man grunts]
- Special delivery for the Führer.</i>

38:23.701 --> 38:25.760
[in Italian] Holy Mother of God.

39:05.509 --> 39:06.999
Train!

39:09.680 --> 39:11.341
Train!

39:11.382 --> 39:14.408
Train, you damn fool!
I thought you was dead!

39:16.787 --> 39:18.812
[Hector] Told you
he was going over the hill.

39:25.963 --> 39:29.296
[whispering] Oh, no.
The fuck is he...

39:29.333 --> 39:31.801
We wait here till dark,
and then we cross back.

39:31.836 --> 39:33.201
Good.

39:33.237 --> 39:35.535
[speaks Spanish]
This shit is heavy as hell.

39:41.178 --> 39:43.339
Bishop!

39:43.381 --> 39:46.680
- Where you going?
- Y'all go on back across that river.

39:46.717 --> 39:49.686
The only person with any luck
around here is him.

39:49.720 --> 39:52.985
Plus, he owe me $1,400.
That's the kind of money

39:53.023 --> 39:55.355
that can set me up
for the rest of my life.

39:55.393 --> 39:57.384
Even if the rest of my life is today.

40:10.674 --> 40:12.835
[grunts, in Spanish]
To hell with this.

40:15.279 --> 40:16.678
I'm up shit's creek.

40:56.921 --> 41:00.186
- Jesse Owens!
- [Train] Jack Johnson.

41:00.224 --> 41:03.216
You go talk to your wife up there.

41:22.746 --> 41:27.149
I never felt so lonesome
in my whole life, Bishop.

41:27.184 --> 41:31.018
- I been dreaming a lot.
- Yeah.

41:31.055 --> 41:35.958
Nigga, I ain't really interested in your
dreams. I want my motherfucking money.

41:35.993 --> 41:39.224
I got something's
worth more than $1,400.

41:41.031 --> 41:43.795
Better than black cat's bones.
Make you invisible.

41:43.834 --> 41:45.665
Gives the strength of five people!

41:45.703 --> 41:48.399
I think your cheese
done slid off your biscuit.

41:48.439 --> 41:51.738
You never see me chalk the line
for no white kid like you done.

41:51.775 --> 41:54.573
- You told me to!
- I didn't tell you to get us killed.

41:56.480 --> 42:00.746
This uniform don't change nothing for
us. This is a white man's war, Train.

42:00.784 --> 42:05.517
Negroes ain't got nothing to do with
this. This boy ain't got no life nohow.

42:05.556 --> 42:08.650
Why he don't? Hmm?

42:08.692 --> 42:12.753
A life of goodness is not what these
white folk has chosen for they children.

42:12.796 --> 42:15.026
Look at me.

42:16.834 --> 42:20.964
Good book says it, Proverbs 22:16.

42:21.005 --> 42:26.033
"Raise up a child the way you want him
to go, and he will not depart from it."

42:26.076 --> 42:28.044
Now, he's trained to hate.

42:29.980 --> 42:33.279
Shit, his life ain't worth
a dollar of Chinese money.

42:33.317 --> 42:36.013
Listen here, Bishop.

42:36.053 --> 42:39.250
This boy ain't done nothing to you.

42:39.290 --> 42:41.087
Mm-hm.

42:41.125 --> 42:43.821
You didn't want him before, did you?

42:48.966 --> 42:52.527
- Where you goin', Sam Train?
- Hey, Stamps, we movin' or not?

42:57.241 --> 43:00.404
We hold here till night.
Me and Bishop'll take first watch.

43:00.444 --> 43:04.278
Hector, you and Train take second.
Give the boy whatever first aid you got.

43:13.958 --> 43:17.553
What'd you get us into now, Diesel?

43:17.595 --> 43:22.259
It's always something with you,
big fella. Here, you gonna need these.

43:22.299 --> 43:24.733
Come on, kid.
[speaks Italian] Eat.

43:24.768 --> 43:26.167
Eat.

43:27.171 --> 43:29.162
Come on.

43:29.206 --> 43:31.003
He won't take the medicine.

43:37.748 --> 43:39.807
Go on, give it here.

43:39.850 --> 43:42.216
You want some chocolate, boy?

43:45.322 --> 43:48.257
I wouldn't get attached.
He'll be dead in a week.

43:48.292 --> 43:53.252
I ain't never been this close
to a white person before, Hec.

43:53.297 --> 43:56.528
Never even touched one.
Not even a dead one.

43:56.567 --> 43:59.934
If this one dies, I'll give you
a whistle as a consolation prize.

43:59.970 --> 44:02.962
- You really think he'll die?
- Why worry about it?

44:03.007 --> 44:04.998
We could all be dead
in an hour anyway.

44:11.949 --> 44:13.974
Why you always kissing that thing, Hec?

44:14.018 --> 44:18.853
- Reminds me who my father is.
- I don't need help remembering my pa.

44:18.889 --> 44:22.518
His name's Chester.
Chester Train.

44:22.559 --> 44:24.390
Let's give this kid some water.

44:28.766 --> 44:29.790
[in Italian] Water.

44:33.937 --> 44:34.995
Arturo?

44:35.939 --> 44:38.271
Can I ask you something?

44:38.308 --> 44:39.707
What you want, boy?

44:39.743 --> 44:41.643
[in Italian] Can you tell me who I am?

44:42.846 --> 44:45.781
Hector, you speak that Italian?
What's he saying?

44:45.816 --> 44:48.284
He said, "Who am I?"
But who's he talking to?

44:48.318 --> 44:50.343
Lord, I knew it!

44:50.387 --> 44:53.083
I could see it in his face!
Look at him, Hec.

44:53.123 --> 44:54.920
Shh! Quiet down.

44:54.958 --> 44:57.426
Good God!

44:57.461 --> 44:59.361
- He got the power!
- What power?

44:59.396 --> 45:03.423
God knows it. In the olden days,
everything could speak.

45:03.467 --> 45:05.867
- The trees, the birds.
- Shh!

45:05.903 --> 45:10.101
If you could hear them things,
then that mean you had it.

45:13.644 --> 45:18.308
This boy's standing
in the shadow of God, Hector.

45:18.348 --> 45:22.478
Thank you, Jesus! Thank you for standing
on Your holy righteous word, Lord!

45:22.519 --> 45:25.283
Hallelujah! Thank you, Jesus!

45:45.409 --> 45:46.967
As you were.

46:14.371 --> 46:18.000
- General Almond.
- Colonel.

46:18.041 --> 46:20.874
I have a photo you should see, sir.

46:20.911 --> 46:25.007
Forget that a minute. How bad
are the numbers from yesterday?

46:25.048 --> 46:27.642
- Bad, sir.
- And lke gets mad when he gives me

46:27.684 --> 46:30.517
waiters and shoeshine boys
to fight the Krauts with.

46:30.554 --> 46:33.580
Germans are dug in.
And that gun at La Spezia's killing us.

46:33.624 --> 46:38.084
Fifteen thousand colored soldiers.
One in four is a casualty.

46:38.128 --> 46:41.222
And all I'm hearing about
is one goddamned gun?

46:41.265 --> 46:45.167
We have guns, too, here.
Look, see, colonel? I got one.

46:45.202 --> 46:49.832
This colored division...
This is an experiment, Jack.

46:49.873 --> 46:54.936
An experiment. These are the first lady
Eleanor Roosevelt's niggers. Not ours.

46:54.978 --> 46:59.847
- Sir, I respectfully disagree.
- That's why they sent you here, Jack.

46:59.883 --> 47:02.647
To lead me into the New World.

47:04.354 --> 47:08.120
A gift from the Brits.
Taken at 11,000 feet. See?

47:08.158 --> 47:11.650
That's a German buildup at
Lama Di Sotto. Two or three regiments.

47:11.695 --> 47:14.630
- Surprise attack you worried about?
- I hope not.

47:14.665 --> 47:16.462
I got corroboration from a partisan.

47:16.500 --> 47:18.991
Anybody crush grapes
with feet can't be trusted.

47:19.036 --> 47:20.936
Get some Krauts to confirm.

47:20.971 --> 47:23.735
Already working on it, sir.
Captain Rudden!

47:27.077 --> 47:30.672
- Good evening, general.
- Come.

47:30.714 --> 47:34.411
Germans may be planning counter-
offensive down the Serchio Valley.

47:34.451 --> 47:37.443
We need a POW to confirm.
You running patrols there?

47:37.487 --> 47:40.320
George Company has a squad
sitting right in that area.

47:40.357 --> 47:42.621
- How?
- They pushed across the Serchio

47:42.659 --> 47:46.356
beyond Hill Maine at the weak point.
I heard them call for artillery.

47:46.396 --> 47:50.594
Might've broken Jerry's hold
on the river. Captain Nokes didn't fire.

47:50.634 --> 47:53.398
- Why not?
- He couldn't see 'em, sir.

47:53.437 --> 47:55.871
Didn't believe they crossed,
they got hung up.

47:55.906 --> 47:59.342
I had Fox Company positioned
down the river from George Company.

47:59.376 --> 48:02.345
Got pretty hot over there.
Four of 'em right up a mountain.

48:02.379 --> 48:04.609
Got weapons and a radio
if they're alive.

48:04.648 --> 48:07.378
- Who are the four men?
- Shouldn't be hard to find out.

48:07.417 --> 48:09.885
One of them's the biggest Negro
you've ever seen in your life.

48:09.920 --> 48:11.945
Mmm.

48:11.989 --> 48:15.083
Very well then. Dismissed.

48:22.032 --> 48:24.500
[door shuts]

49:19.957 --> 49:22.289
[speaking German]
My God, I've had it.

49:22.326 --> 49:23.850
Come on, it's enough.

49:24.995 --> 49:26.019
Yeah, let's go.

49:27.831 --> 49:29.298
I need something to eat.

49:30.634 --> 49:34.695
[speaking Italian]
The Germans are leaving!

49:35.839 --> 49:38.637
[bell tolling]

49:44.448 --> 49:48.111
[speaking German] Push it up
or I'll kill it right now.

49:48.151 --> 49:49.982
I'm pushing as hard
as I can.

49:50.020 --> 49:51.749
Pull, pull, pull.

49:51.788 --> 49:54.689
My goodness I'm hungry.

49:54.725 --> 49:58.991
Finally something to chew on,
rather than the slime they feed us.

50:02.933 --> 50:05.231
[in Italian] Goodbye meat.
Now there'll be nothing left.

50:05.268 --> 50:07.634
They won't get fat on it.

50:07.671 --> 50:09.229
Let's hope they choke on it.

50:09.272 --> 50:11.832
Shut up, the two of you!

50:11.875 --> 50:15.140
Now, let's see if your husband
will come back from Russia.

50:22.853 --> 50:24.320
Mary, Joseph, Jesus,

50:24.354 --> 50:27.118
tell us if we'll see him
or never see him again.

50:27.157 --> 50:28.647
Is he still alive?

50:28.692 --> 50:30.660
My eyes aren't
what they used to be.

50:30.694 --> 50:32.992
- [rattling table]
- Come on!

50:33.030 --> 50:34.327
So, so, so?

50:34.364 --> 50:37.697
We can't even joke? Come on.

50:39.102 --> 50:41.127
That thing is just a stupid kid's game.

50:41.171 --> 50:43.196
You're the usual scoundrel!

50:43.240 --> 50:45.640
Just because he carries
the Fascist Party card,

50:45.675 --> 50:46.699
he thinks he can do what he wants.

50:46.743 --> 50:48.210
Oh yes?

50:48.245 --> 50:51.612
Then who was it who took butter
from the Germans the other day?

50:51.648 --> 50:52.740
The Pope?

50:52.783 --> 50:54.842
Maybe, because it wasn't us.

50:54.885 --> 50:56.182
And the light?

50:56.219 --> 50:57.777
How did your electricity come back on?

50:57.821 --> 50:58.981
Papa.

50:59.022 --> 51:00.182
Come with me.

51:00.223 --> 51:01.247
Come with me.

51:02.225 --> 51:03.783
How did the light come back on?

51:03.827 --> 51:06.660
The truth will never
come out of his mouth.

51:16.139 --> 51:18.300
You would think that
after all these years,

51:18.341 --> 51:20.969
you would treat your friends better.

51:21.011 --> 51:23.377
What is wrong with you, Papa?

51:23.413 --> 51:24.505
Would you tell me?

51:28.952 --> 51:30.681
It's Natalina.

51:30.720 --> 51:32.153
What did she do?

51:32.189 --> 51:34.054
She put the evil eye on me, that Witch.

51:34.091 --> 51:36.423
You still going on about the same story?

51:36.460 --> 51:39.691
The Germans stole your rabbits, not her.

51:41.231 --> 51:44.098
There's strange things going on.

51:44.134 --> 51:46.602
My electricity returned...

51:46.636 --> 51:48.536
from God knows where
after two and a half years.

51:48.572 --> 51:50.233
I was going to ask you about that.

51:50.273 --> 51:53.970
Now I'm lit up like a carnival...

51:54.010 --> 51:57.741
for every bandit and German to see.

51:57.781 --> 52:01.444
It's Natalina's fault. She wants to see
me dead and buried behind the Church.

52:01.485 --> 52:02.884
What are you talking about?

52:04.654 --> 52:06.451
She prays for you every day.

52:08.625 --> 52:09.853
Know what I say?

52:11.061 --> 52:16.158
You go back in there
and apologize to your friends.

52:16.199 --> 52:18.531
Tell everyone that
Mussolini disgusts you,

52:18.568 --> 52:21.298
and that you are not a Fascist anymore.

52:21.338 --> 52:25.502
Il Duce made us a world power again.

52:25.542 --> 52:28.375
His only mistake was to get in bed
with that imbecile Hitler.

52:28.411 --> 52:30.971
Papa, II Duce betrayed Italy.

52:31.014 --> 52:33.778
And now you'll see
how this is going to end.

52:33.817 --> 52:36.115
You are still so young, my child.

52:36.153 --> 52:38.053
You don't know the ways of the world.

52:38.088 --> 52:40.579
But you will learn.

52:40.624 --> 52:42.717
And from whom?

52:42.759 --> 52:44.090
From a Fascist like you?

52:45.095 --> 52:47.222
You're just like your mother.

52:47.264 --> 52:48.993
And she used to tell you
that Blackshirts

52:49.032 --> 52:50.932
are only good for hiding dirt.

52:50.967 --> 52:52.127
Okay, let's go.

52:56.173 --> 52:57.868
[knocking on door]

52:59.309 --> 53:00.674
Germans!!!

53:02.379 --> 53:03.471
It's your house.

53:14.357 --> 53:15.483
Holy Mother of God.

53:23.233 --> 53:24.564
It's okay.

53:24.601 --> 53:26.569
It's okay.

53:26.603 --> 53:27.695
It's okay, it's okay.

53:30.974 --> 53:33.602
Hector, ask who's in charge.
Tell them we're Americans.

53:37.714 --> 53:39.204
[in Italian] Americans?

53:39.249 --> 53:41.274
[in English] Me, too. Half.

53:41.318 --> 53:42.580
[in Italian] Half.

53:42.619 --> 53:45.213
[in English] Me sister Ida, half.

53:45.255 --> 53:48.019
[in Italian] We called her little Ida,
because she was the baby.

53:48.058 --> 53:50.322
Put us together,
we make one American.

53:50.360 --> 53:51.793
[in Italian] Okay, wait. Wait.

53:51.828 --> 53:54.695
Wait. Wait. Wait.

53:54.731 --> 53:55.959
Thank you.

53:55.999 --> 53:57.261
Who's in charge here?

54:09.145 --> 54:11.613
Anybody here speak English?

54:14.150 --> 54:15.412
[in Italian]
Where are the Germans?

54:15.452 --> 54:18.683
Everywhere. Boom, boom.

54:18.722 --> 54:21.452
My name is Renata.

54:23.360 --> 54:28.263
- Where'd you learn English?
- I was nanny for a British family.

54:28.298 --> 54:32.860
And a jolly good tuck-in-the-bed
tinkerer you must be.

54:32.902 --> 54:36.838
- You can nanny me. Want a Camel?
- Cool it, Bishop.

54:36.873 --> 54:41.037
I'm Staff Sergeant Aubrey Stamps.
We got a boy that needs help.

54:41.077 --> 54:42.806
[in Italian]
A boy? He has a boy.

54:45.015 --> 54:46.505
Oh, my God.

54:47.484 --> 54:49.577
Is he alive? Put him here.

54:49.619 --> 54:51.211
Slow. Slowly.

54:53.323 --> 54:55.052
Where did you find him?

54:55.091 --> 54:57.286
[Hector] On the Mountain.
Do you know him?

54:57.327 --> 54:59.386
[Natalina]
No, I don't know him.

54:59.429 --> 55:01.897
But he can stay here
until he gets better.

55:01.931 --> 55:05.128
Tell them we're taking the boy
to a hospital. They can come.

55:05.168 --> 55:08.399
They need to evacuate.
We'll escort them down the mountain.

55:08.438 --> 55:11.202
[in Italian] We're going to a hospital.
You can come with us.

55:12.075 --> 55:14.134
The hospital around the corner?

55:14.177 --> 55:16.372
The Germans are everywhere.

55:16.413 --> 55:18.438
Torrite, Rontano, Mezzana.

55:18.481 --> 55:20.949
All the way to Barga
and down to the Serchio.

55:20.984 --> 55:23.782
I don't know how you
got past Vergemoli.

55:23.820 --> 55:27.483
The only way to Pietrasanta...

55:27.524 --> 55:29.185
where the Americans might be...

55:29.225 --> 55:30.749
is over that way,

55:31.761 --> 55:33.786
over the Mountain of the Sleeping Man.

55:35.031 --> 55:36.259
Says we're surrounded.

55:36.299 --> 55:38.460
Doesn't know how we got
past German lines,

55:38.501 --> 55:41.732
but the only way we might find
some Americans is up there.

55:41.771 --> 55:44.137
- The Mountain of the Sleeping Man.
- Sleeping Man?

55:44.174 --> 55:47.575
- [in Italian] What is that?
- It's a legend.

55:47.610 --> 55:53.571
A shepherd fell in love with a girl
who would not love him back.

55:53.616 --> 55:56.312
So he lays across the Mountain...

55:56.353 --> 55:58.753
to protect her from the wind and rain.

55:58.788 --> 56:02.986
He still lies there today,
to protect us all.

56:03.026 --> 56:07.395
Legend has it that
one day he will awaken.

56:10.166 --> 56:12.726
A legend about a shepherd
that fell in love...

56:12.769 --> 56:15.067
Whatever she's saying,
we gotta rest until sunup.

56:15.105 --> 56:17.369
- OK.
- Stay here? No, no.

56:17.407 --> 56:19.136
<i>Stay here. Si, si.</i>

56:19.175 --> 56:22.167
If they sing to the Krauts,
we will pull a trigger on this

56:22.212 --> 56:26.046
and tell the hammer to hurry. Won't be
nothing but powder and steel here.

56:26.082 --> 56:29.643
We are not Germans.
We are Italians.

56:29.686 --> 56:32.052
- Full blood.
- And what are we? Half blood?

56:34.657 --> 56:36.955
[in Italian]
We should take him...

56:36.993 --> 56:38.722
and put him to bed.

56:38.762 --> 56:41.993
The boy stays here. He's sick.

56:59.082 --> 57:00.549
<i>Heil Hitler!</i>

57:30.079 --> 57:32.809
[in German]
Catching up on your reading?

57:32.849 --> 57:35.977
Yes, Colonel, I'm informing myself
about the enemy.

57:36.019 --> 57:40.353
The Partisans often take their names
from banned poetry and literature.

57:40.390 --> 57:42.358
This helps us identify them.

57:42.392 --> 57:44.587
Who is the poet?

57:44.627 --> 57:46.356
Giovanni Pascoli.

57:46.396 --> 57:51.857
Do you think it's appropriate
to waste your time reading poetry?

57:51.901 --> 57:57.771
In the past nine months we've seen
a sharp rise in Partisan activity.

57:57.807 --> 58:00.105
What are you planning to do about it?

58:00.143 --> 58:04.204
Colonel, we are down
to shovels and mule shit.

58:04.247 --> 58:05.714
My men are exhausted.

58:05.748 --> 58:07.943
We need ammo and food.

58:07.984 --> 58:10.612
Food? You want food?

58:10.653 --> 58:13.349
You can suck icicles
in Russia...

58:13.389 --> 58:18.725
like you did before your so-called
neck wound brought you back here.

58:18.761 --> 58:22.322
You think you're the first
to command hungry troops?

58:22.365 --> 58:25.528
I mean no disrespect, Colonel.

58:27.203 --> 58:30.502
Good. Listen closely.

58:30.540 --> 58:33.407
I have come too far to repeat myself.

58:33.443 --> 58:37.709
First, there is a peasant, a terrorist.

58:37.747 --> 58:42.480
Named The Great Butterfly.
He's causing many problems.

58:42.519 --> 58:45.147
He's hiding in these mountains.
Find him.

58:45.188 --> 58:48.453
When he is found,
issue Directive Bandenbefehl...

58:48.491 --> 58:51.153
to him and his criminal friends.

58:51.194 --> 58:52.252
Bandenbefehl?

58:52.295 --> 58:54.923
Is there an echo out here?

58:54.964 --> 58:59.094
General Kesselring's standing
field order for the Italian Republic.

58:59.135 --> 59:01.626
At a commander's sole discretion,

59:01.671 --> 59:04.469
for every one German soldier killed,

59:04.507 --> 59:06.873
we execute ten Italian civilians.

59:06.910 --> 59:12.439
You should have been capable to execute
that order at least once in nine months.

59:12.482 --> 59:16.111
Colonel, with all due respect,
if I execute this order...

59:16.152 --> 59:18.677
my men would kill innocent civilians.

59:18.721 --> 59:22.350
It would be a violation
of the Geneva Convention.

59:22.392 --> 59:27.159
Partisans are not civilians;
they are terrorists.

59:27.196 --> 59:30.131
They are not protected
under the Geneva Convention.

59:30.166 --> 59:32.532
Bandenbefehl!

59:32.569 --> 59:33.729
Bandenbefehl.

59:36.072 --> 59:39.439
Secondly, the surprise
counterattack is still planned.

59:39.475 --> 59:43.969
I will tighten supply lines
with food and ammunition.

59:44.013 --> 59:46.311
And three:

59:46.349 --> 59:50.217
A delicate intelligence matter
of the utmost priority.

59:56.159 --> 59:59.026
We are missing a Corporal...

59:59.062 --> 01:00:02.691
from the 35th Regiment,
2nd Battalion, 5th Company.

01:00:02.732 --> 01:00:06.725
Name: Hans Brandt,
gone AWOL three weeks ago.

01:00:06.769 --> 01:00:09.738
[Eichholz] We have some every day.
What's so special about him?

01:00:10.673 --> 01:00:13.141
You and I are not here...

01:00:13.176 --> 01:00:17.010
to question the Führer's orders.

01:00:17.046 --> 01:00:19.606
You are to send out a search party.

01:00:19.649 --> 01:00:21.139
Find him.

01:00:21.184 --> 01:00:22.879
Don't let him escape.

01:00:22.919 --> 01:00:24.910
And when you have him...

01:00:25.955 --> 01:00:28.822
get word to me immediately.

01:00:37.967 --> 01:00:39.696
Let's go!

01:00:50.680 --> 01:00:54.275
<i>[in Italian] If I am no longer
that lamp...</i>

01:00:54.317 --> 01:00:57.115
<i>which flickers in front
of a sweet Maria.</i>

01:00:57.153 --> 01:00:58.620
[in German] What does that mean?

01:00:59.856 --> 01:01:01.653
God help this poor bastard Brandt.

01:01:02.525 --> 01:01:03.924
Whatever he's done,

01:01:03.960 --> 01:01:06.827
it's no worse than what anyone else
has done in this war.

01:01:07.563 --> 01:01:08.928
Mount a search party.

01:01:08.965 --> 01:01:10.956
We have to find him first,

01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:13.992
hold him and give him a few days...

01:01:14.037 --> 01:01:17.131
before Pflueger pulls out
his teeth, one by one.

01:01:17.173 --> 01:01:18.197
Yes.

01:01:18.641 --> 01:01:21.007
I'll be relieved when this war is over.

01:01:21.044 --> 01:01:22.909
I want to return to my family.

01:01:51.941 --> 01:01:54.136
[in Italian]
I've watched you grow up.

01:01:54.177 --> 01:01:56.441
But you haven't become much.

01:01:56.479 --> 01:01:57.946
And he can't do much.

01:01:57.980 --> 01:01:59.845
- You're laughing at me?
- Of course.

01:01:59.882 --> 01:02:02.350
Where did you get that?

01:02:02.385 --> 01:02:03.875
So many things you want to know.

01:02:03.920 --> 01:02:05.012
Here. Take it and eat.

01:02:05.054 --> 01:02:06.385
Give me some, too.

01:02:06.422 --> 01:02:08.686
Are you afraid you're
not going to get any?

01:02:08.725 --> 01:02:09.885
Here. Grow.

01:02:09.926 --> 01:02:11.553
Give me a chestnut, too.

01:02:13.229 --> 01:02:15.026
My goodness, you stink like a sheep.

01:02:15.064 --> 01:02:16.725
Hey, leave me alone.

01:02:16.766 --> 01:02:18.700
Aren't you the dandy?

01:02:18.735 --> 01:02:20.498
Ah, he's offended.

01:02:25.875 --> 01:02:28.503
What the fuck are you doing, Peppi?

01:02:28.544 --> 01:02:30.239
You have to be on the lookout.

01:02:30.279 --> 01:02:33.510
If I had been a German,
you would all be dead... 1, 2, 3.

01:02:33.549 --> 01:02:35.176
I almost choked.

01:02:36.219 --> 01:02:37.846
You wait here.

01:02:53.069 --> 01:02:54.331
My friend.

01:02:54.370 --> 01:02:56.634
The Americans are getting closer.

01:02:57.907 --> 01:02:59.898
We have to warn them about
the Germans' counterattack.

01:02:59.942 --> 01:03:02.069
They know it already, for sure.

01:03:03.146 --> 01:03:05.171
You? How are you?

01:03:05.214 --> 01:03:07.444
Me? I'm okay.

01:03:07.483 --> 01:03:08.541
You?

01:03:08.584 --> 01:03:11.075
I always have Marco's
face in front of my eyes.

01:03:14.423 --> 01:03:15.651
Don't worry about that.

01:03:15.691 --> 01:03:20.924
My brother is dead.
Nobody cares about him any more.

01:03:20.963 --> 01:03:22.089
I care.

01:03:22.131 --> 01:03:23.530
In your opinion...

01:03:24.433 --> 01:03:25.832
when we will be in front of God,

01:03:25.868 --> 01:03:28.701
if we ever get there,

01:03:28.738 --> 01:03:31.707
is he going to ask us
for our political card?

01:03:31.741 --> 01:03:34.710
Is he going to say,
"Marco, no... Ludovico, no.

01:03:34.744 --> 01:03:38.236
You're not allowed in
because you're Fascists."

01:03:38.281 --> 01:03:42.877
What's the difference between
us and them in the eyes of God?

01:03:42.919 --> 01:03:45.183
You're asking yourself
too many questions.

01:03:45.221 --> 01:03:48.816
If you think too much,
it will drive you crazy.

01:03:48.858 --> 01:03:51.452
And then who will kill the Germans?

01:03:51.494 --> 01:03:52.518
Hey.

01:03:54.764 --> 01:03:57.164
Anyway, what's done is done.

01:04:05.007 --> 01:04:09.307
George Company to 370,
George Company to 3-7, over.

01:04:13.649 --> 01:04:16.243
George Company to 370, over.

01:04:40.042 --> 01:04:42.738
[in Italian] Someone tell that
big beast to get out of my room.

01:04:42.778 --> 01:04:45.838
Shh! The Boy has a fever.

01:04:45.882 --> 01:04:48.510
He needs to eat and get some rest.

01:04:48.551 --> 01:04:50.542
Try thinking of others
every once in awhile.

01:05:00.463 --> 01:05:01.760
Arturo.

01:05:02.832 --> 01:05:05.300
The Chocolate Giant's Castle...

01:05:05.334 --> 01:05:07.165
if you could only see it.

01:05:07.203 --> 01:05:09.694
It's enormous.

01:05:09.739 --> 01:05:11.900
No, even bigger.

01:05:12.742 --> 01:05:15.302
Of course I saw it.

01:05:15.344 --> 01:05:17.471
It's all made of chocolate.

01:05:17.513 --> 01:05:19.481
You break a piece off,

01:05:19.515 --> 01:05:21.312
and it grows back.

01:05:23.452 --> 01:05:25.716
Yes, I did save a piece for you.

01:05:33.195 --> 01:05:34.685
Good heavens.

01:05:34.730 --> 01:05:36.220
Something's not right.

01:05:36.265 --> 01:05:37.664
Someone put the evil eye on him.

01:05:37.700 --> 01:05:39.998
Bewitched or not, he's got to go.

01:05:40.036 --> 01:05:42.869
- To where?
- With the Americans.

01:05:42.905 --> 01:05:44.566
I think he brings good luck.
The Boy stays.

01:05:44.607 --> 01:05:46.234
This is my house.

01:05:46.275 --> 01:05:47.640
I have a house too.

01:05:48.611 --> 01:05:50.010
Natalina.

01:05:50.046 --> 01:05:51.536
What do you think?

01:05:51.580 --> 01:05:54.640
I say this Boy is talking to the Devil.

01:05:54.684 --> 01:05:56.208
We need a Priest here.

01:05:56.252 --> 01:05:58.413
He doesn't need a Priest.
He needs a Doctor.

01:05:58.454 --> 01:06:01.321
A Priest can take
the Devil out of him.

01:06:01.357 --> 01:06:04.383
Train, get up. We gotta book.

01:06:08.898 --> 01:06:10.092
[Train] Excuse me.

01:06:10.132 --> 01:06:13.568
Hey, boy. Hey.

01:06:13.602 --> 01:06:17.663
Time for you
to take your medicine again.

01:06:18.474 --> 01:06:20.032
Here it comes. Ready?

01:06:20.076 --> 01:06:22.738
[humming]

01:06:23.779 --> 01:06:26.270
There. Thank you.

01:06:27.950 --> 01:06:30.009
Get you some of that soup, boy.

01:06:31.087 --> 01:06:32.179
Mmm.

01:06:36.826 --> 01:06:39.624
- Yes.
- He would not eat before.

01:06:42.765 --> 01:06:44.323
Here you go, boy.

01:06:46.202 --> 01:06:48.136
It's all over your shirt.

01:06:50.873 --> 01:06:54.434
- Come on, boy. Let's go.
- [in Italian] My Chocolate Giant.

01:06:54.477 --> 01:06:58.345
- OK, sarge. We ready.
- Oh, hold on, hold on, hold on.

01:06:58.381 --> 01:07:01.282
We? Boy, where the hell "we" goin'?

01:07:01.317 --> 01:07:03.410
You wasn't chiseling him,
we wouldn't be here.

01:07:03.452 --> 01:07:06.080
- You think Nokes is lookin' for us?
- What?

01:07:07.656 --> 01:07:10.420
Hector been tryin' to fix that radio
since we got here.

01:07:10.459 --> 01:07:12.222
- Shh!
- What?

01:07:16.065 --> 01:07:17.657
<i>Arrive- damn-derci.</i>

01:07:23.005 --> 01:07:28.375
Hector. We gotta bail. Ask the old man
if he'll show us another way outta here.

01:07:28.411 --> 01:07:31.812
- Maybe we can reach the 366.
- We can't get five feet outta here

01:07:31.847 --> 01:07:34.645
<i>without being flavor of the week
for the Guten Tags.</i>

01:07:34.683 --> 01:07:38.642
<i>These people survived for years
without mortars. Stay with the paisans.</i>

01:07:38.687 --> 01:07:41.986
You wanna stay here and play house,
go ahead, but I'm bookin'.

01:07:42.024 --> 01:07:45.619
Ask the old man if he'll show us
another way outta these mountains.

01:07:45.661 --> 01:07:50.291
Tell him we'll pay him. We got plenty of
that funny money they use around here.

01:07:50.332 --> 01:07:52.493
[speaks Italian]
Can you show us a safe path?

01:07:52.535 --> 01:07:54.400
There is no safe way.

01:07:54.437 --> 01:07:56.064
Germans. Boom! Boom!

01:07:56.264 --> 01:07:57.822
You know a way.

01:07:57.865 --> 01:08:01.062
Franco was the mailman,
ask him. I'm too old.

01:08:01.102 --> 01:08:04.469
Me? I have to deliver the mail.

01:08:04.505 --> 01:08:06.564
What mail, you old crazy fool?

01:08:06.608 --> 01:08:10.271
Old crazy fool? You're the old crazy,
like your mother and your father.

01:08:10.311 --> 01:08:12.541
- I know.
- You know?

01:08:12.580 --> 01:08:15.913
I know a way. I take you.

01:08:15.950 --> 01:08:17.417
[in Italian] What did you say?

01:08:19.687 --> 01:08:22.019
What did my daughter say?

01:08:22.055 --> 01:08:24.854
[in Italian] I have
nothing to do with this.

01:08:24.892 --> 01:08:27.587
Bishop. What you think?

01:08:27.629 --> 01:08:31.429
Little Red Riding Hood
lead us through the woods?

01:08:31.466 --> 01:08:33.934
I don't know, sarge.

01:08:33.968 --> 01:08:38.268
I mean, she fine. Man, she fine.

01:08:38.305 --> 01:08:42.332
I hear that they got
lady Mussolinis, too.

01:08:42.377 --> 01:08:44.345
Could be a trap.

01:08:46.948 --> 01:08:48.939
Hector.

01:08:48.983 --> 01:08:51.383
You the boss, staff sergeant.

01:08:51.419 --> 01:08:54.183
No good. No. No good.

01:08:55.622 --> 01:08:58.990
All of a sudden the old man
speaks some English, huh?

01:09:02.095 --> 01:09:03.586
[in Italian] Are you crazy in the head?

01:09:03.631 --> 01:09:05.029
Keep out of this.

01:09:05.899 --> 01:09:07.424
I forbid you to go.

01:09:07.468 --> 01:09:10.562
I don't need your permission.
Understand?

01:09:10.604 --> 01:09:12.800
You're still my daughter.

01:09:12.840 --> 01:09:16.799
Look, we'll find a way
outta here. Let's go.

01:09:28.756 --> 01:09:31.316
<i>Bye-bye, Americani.</i>

01:09:31.359 --> 01:09:33.327
Renata. Come away.

01:09:33.361 --> 01:09:34.555
No!

01:09:35.830 --> 01:09:38.060
Oh!

01:09:38.099 --> 01:09:42.001
Cigarette? Chocolate?

01:09:42.036 --> 01:09:43.765
[Stamps] Hell, no!

01:09:46.174 --> 01:09:47.698
[in Italian] Shove it up your ass.

01:09:49.810 --> 01:09:53.907
Sergeant Stamps out there
fussin' over what side to get back to.

01:09:53.948 --> 01:09:57.111
It don't mean nothin', boy.

01:09:57.151 --> 01:09:59.619
Me, I ain't got a side.

01:10:03.124 --> 01:10:06.821
[speaking Italian] Arturo said
that if you turn your head...

01:10:06.861 --> 01:10:08.453
it will be my birthday.

01:10:08.496 --> 01:10:12.557
I'll get toys and lots of candy.

01:10:12.600 --> 01:10:14.932
Now, please turn your head.

01:10:15.903 --> 01:10:17.894
Please turn your head.

01:10:19.507 --> 01:10:23.238
I can't understand your words, boy.

01:10:23.277 --> 01:10:25.177
But I don't need to.

01:10:25.213 --> 01:10:30.150
You see, everything you touch,
you brings good to it. You do.

01:10:31.552 --> 01:10:35.079
See this little thing here?
lt'll make you invisible.

01:10:35.123 --> 01:10:40.823
Give you the strength of five people.
You ain't got to own nothin'.

01:10:40.862 --> 01:10:43.490
Ain't got to be a big somebody.

